President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Jonathan Kanter as Assistant Attorney General for the Antitrust Division at the Department of Justice. Kanter is a distinguished antitrust lawyer with over 20 years of experience and has been a leading advocate for strong antitrust enforcement and competition policy. He currently works as a partner at The Kanter Law Group LLP, a boutique antitrust law firm. Kanter previously served as Co-Chair of the antitrust practice at Paul, Weiss, Rifkind, Wharton, and Garrison LLP, as well as an attorney for the U.S. Federal Trade Commission's Bureau of Competition. He holds a J.D. from Washington University in St. Louis and a B.A. from the State University of New York at Albany.